0 ===== "Ball" on top — approximated as a 2x2 brick. Note: the
0 ball's colour is contextually different from the body (rules
0 say red bodies have blue balls, black bodies have red balls).
0 With the lego_prop color override applying to ALL bricks in
0 the .ldr, we can't easily get a different colour for the ball.
0 For now the whole thing is one colour; refine via separate
0 .ldr files (senior_barrier_red, senior_barrier_black) if the
0 ball colour mismatch is visually important.
